attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This MIPS binary is a malicious botnet agent, likely a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt (Bashlite) families, targeted at IoT devices. The sample exhibits classic malware behaviors including anti-analysis via VMware detection (sub_400960), the use of a local lock file (/tmp/.bot_lock) to ensure single instance execution, and an aggressive process scanner (sub_4026e4) that monitors /proc to identify and terminate competing processes or security tools. The core functionality includes a comprehensive suite of DDoS modules (sub_40559c) supporting multiple attack vectors such as SYN floods, ACK floods, UDP floods, HTTP floods, ICMP floods, and GRE floods. It features a persistent C2 communication loop and uses a hardcoded User-Agent for HTTP-based attacks and telemetry.
